    "Each stage plays a distinct role in gradually aligning modalities, expanding task capabilities, and fine-tuning the model to follow human intent.",
    "However, not all models necessarily undergo all three stages; the actual training stages employed depend on each model's intended capabilities.",
    "The organization of this section will primarily follow these three stages of training for Speech LLMs with continuous sequence modeling.",
    "At the end of this section, we briefly discuss how models based on discrete speech tokens differ in their training approach.",
    "A. Modality AlignmentAt the outset, Speech LLMs must learn a shared representation between spoken input and text."
